public abstract class AbstractGUIWidget
extends org.mt4j.components.MTComponent

This abstract class represents a Widgets and defines the standard interface of a GUI-Component and also common animations.

removeListenerType

public boolean removeListenerType(java.lang.Class<? extends org.mt4j.input.inputProcessors.IInputProcessor> gestureEvtSender,
                                  java.lang.Class<? extends org.mt4j.input.inputProcessors.IGestureEventListener> listenerType)
This method lets you delete one (and only one) GestureEventListener On this GUI-component. You do not have to catch the concrete listener-object and then delete it manually, so you only have to know its type.

Parameters:
gestureEvtSender - The sender of the gesture event as a Class which implements IInputProcessor.
listenerType - The type of the gesture event as a Class which implements IGestureEventListener.
Returns:
Returns TRUE, if a gesture event listener was removed, otherwise, if there was no such gesture event listener found, returns FALSE.

getVectorNextToComponent

public org.mt4j.util.math.Vector3D getVectorNextToComponent(float clearance,
                                                            boolean horizontal)
Returns a position beneath or next to this component that can be used as a position for other components. You just have to specify the distance between the new vector and the method callee and if you want this new vector shifted horizontally to the callee's position or vertically.

Parameters:
clearance - The distance between the vector to create and this object as a float.
horizontal - Indicates, whether you want the new point to be shifted horizontal direction to this component's position or otherwise in vertical direction. Horizontal direction means, that the y-value of the new vector will be the same as the one of the positiono of this element, it behaves analoguous to the x-value in the vertical case, that is, if you specify this parameter as FALSE.
Returns:
A new Vector3D that is positioned either On the same height as this component's position vector or On the same width respectively.

setPositionNextTo

public void setPositionNextTo(AbstractGUIWidget comp,
                              float clearance,
                              boolean horizontal)
Sets the position of this component next to the position of another component, using a specified clearing area. Furthermore, you can specify of this component shall be aligned under or left to the specified component.

Parameters:
comp - The AbstractGUIComponent to which this component shall be positioned next to.
clearance - The free distance between the specified component and this one.
horizontal - Indicates, whether you want the new point to be shifted horizontal direction to this component's position or otherwise in vertical direction. Horizontal direction means, that the y-value of the new vector will be the same as the one of the positiono of this element, it behaves analoguous to the x-value in the vertical case, that is, if you specify this parameter as FALSE.

setPosOnScreen

public org.mt4j.util.math.Vector3D setPosOnScreen(float x,
                                                  float y)
Sets the position of this AbstractGUIComponent to the specified screen coordinates On the z=0 Plane.
If the position-anchor is defined as the center of the AbstractGUIComponent or a specified corner depends On the concrete type of object to handle.

Parameters:
x - The normalized x-position On the screen, where 0 is the left edge and 1 is the right edge as a float
y - The normalized y-position On the screen, where 0 is the upper edge and 1 is the lower edged as a float
Returns:
Returns the new global position as a Vector3D or null in case of error

setPosInParent

public org.mt4j.util.math.Vector3D setPosInParent(float x,
                                                  float y)
Sets the position of this AbstractGUIComponent to the specified screen coordinates within the parents On the z=0 Plane.
If the position-anchor is defined as the center of the AbstractGUIComponent or a specified corner depends On the concrete type of object to handle. Caution: If the specific AbstractGUIComponent is able to fulfill the request depends On the parent's type.

Following parent-types are supported by now:
-MTRectangle
-AbstractGUIComponent
-(augment if you want)

Parameters:
x - The normalized x-position On the parent, where 0 is the left edge and 1 is the right edge as a float
y - The normalized y-position On the parent, where 0 is the upper edge and 1 is the lower edged as a float
Returns:
Returns the new global position as a Vector3D or null in case of error

setEnabled

public void setEnabled(boolean b)
Sets this component's mode into disabled, when the argument is FALSE. If the argument is TRUE and the mode is "disabled", then it will be enabled, more specific, it will be changed to "axis". If b is TRUE and this component has another state like "disabled", nothing happens.

Specified by:
setEnabled in interface org.mt4j.components.interfaces.IMTComponent
